description.plain:
Known from his fast rise in the Greek hip-hop scene, his stormy lyricism, and the iconic representation of the Western Athens street life, “Trannos”, is already one of Trapsion’s most promising talents. Despite his young age, he managed to release several trap bangers just within the first months of his music involvement. Even though he began writing lyrics for fun, he soon saw fan love and appreciation thanks to his spontaneous attitude and lyrical roughness.
Mainly influenced by Greek Trap music pioneer Billy Sio, it was a big surprise for Trannos when Sio’s manager Stefanos Karasarinis approached him. The rest is history as Trannos joined  Trapsion Entertainment next to label’s founder Billy Sio and a dynamic roster of promising rappers like Skam, Skliros. He rapidly rose to success with his first hit “GTPM” featuring the entire Trapsion roster, followed by the “street sensation” EP “Fotia‘’ and the dominating trap hit AMG (featuring ATC Nico) which topped the Greek charts. His 2021 collaboration with Greek rap stars Billy Sio & Light titled Agria Zwa was a huge milestone in Trannos' career. His latest singles Coco and Mavro Gyali became huge hits.
